                            <p class="text-left">Refund policies for event registration can vary widely depending on the
                                organizer and the type of event. However, here
                                are some common elements you might find in refund policies:</p>

                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Full Refund:</strong> Some organizers offer a full refund if you cancel your
                                    registration within a certain period before the
                                    event. This period can vary, but it's typically several weeks or months before the
                                    event
                                    date.</li>
                                <li><strong>Partial Refund:</strong> In some cases, organizers may offer a partial
                                    refund if
                                    you cancel within a specific time frame. The
                                    amount refunded can vary and is often based on how far in advance you cancel.</li>
                                <li><strong>No Refund:</strong> Some events have a strict no-refund policy, especially
                                    for
                                    special or high-demand events where space is
                                    limited, and they may have turned away other potential attendees.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Transferable Registration:</strong> Instead of providing refunds, some
                                    organizers allow you to transfer your registration to
                                    another person. This can be a convenient option if you can't attend but know someone
                                    who
                                    can take your place.</li>
                                <li><strong>Event Cancellation:</strong> If the organizer cancels the event for any
                                    reason,
                                    they may offer full or partial refunds to all
                                    registered attendees. This policy should be clearly outlined in the event terms and
                                    conditions.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Force Majeure Clause:</strong> Event organizers often include a force
                                    majeure
                                    clause in their terms and conditions. This clause
                                    typically states that they are not responsible for refunds if the event is canceled
                                    due
                                    to circumstances beyond their
                                    control, such as natural disasters or government restrictions.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Processing Fees:</strong> Some organizers may deduct processing fees from
                                    the
                                    refunded amount, especially if you paid using a
                                    credit card or other payment methods that charge transaction fees.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Tiered Refund Schedule:</strong> For multi-day events or events with
                                    multiple
                                    ticket tiers, organizers may have a tiered refund
                                    schedule, with different refund amounts depending on when you cancel and the type of
                                    ticket you purchased.
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Refund Request Process:</strong> The policy should also outline the process
                                    for
                                    requesting a refund, such as who to contact and
                                    the deadline for submitting refund requests.
                                </li>
